text: Rainer Küchl is an Austrian musician. He plays the violin and is a music professor. He started to play the violin at the age of 11. At the age of 14, he studied music at the University of Music and Performing Arts, Vienna. He became the concertmaster of the Vienna Philharmonic at the age of 20. In 1973 he founded the Küchl Quartett which is known as the Wiener Musikverein Quartett. == Other websites == * Rainer Küchl Official Website * Vienna Philharmonic Orchestra * Vienna Musikverein * Küchl Biography Category:1950 births Category:Living people Category:Austrian violinists Category:Concertmasters
